      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical decision criterion and regulatory acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate. This quantity directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.0 used in 510(k) submissions for Class II CPB devices. The QoI is computed from the same scalar transport field validated against experimental data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
